There would be even less accidents - one is expected to prevent any four accidents with individual injuries - as soon as the so-called smart emergency brake systems become popular.
Then the vehicle is equipped with a system that identifies obstacles (via a radar or a camera) and warns the driver, while already carrying light pressure on the brakes.
