Cost proposal of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost proposal in just four steps: ID of the vehicle, search for the spare parts, creating and creating a cost proposal.
Easy handling of these systems is a basic condition, especially to convince older professionals who are usually more or less against the use of these new computer technologies.
The database includes 1.034 vehicles, 666 of which include passenger cars, 109 ground cars, 137 motorcycles, 78 small cars and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with Internet connection to use.
After the repair model has been identified using the vehicle number, a graphic of the respective model appears and the required spare part is then selected.
The user may include variables, such as the price for working hours, fees or discounts, and may then print the cost proposal and communicate to its customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for evaluation such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workplace targeted does not include estimated working hours.
The use costs for this tool are €350 per year, a amount that the customer can pay without any further.
